File: Hypertension, diabetes and cardiac disease are the three most common co-morbidities associated with serious illness from COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG - On Sunday, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa was announced as 6,783 by the Department of Health. Eight more people have died as a result of the virus, two from the Western Cape, four from the Eastern Cape, and two from Gauteng. READ: COVID-19 death toll in SA rises to 123 7, 216 777 citizens have been screened and from that Community Screening Programme 72,087 were referred for testing, the Department said. Hypertension, diabetes and cardiac disease are the three most common co-morbidities associated with serious illness from COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.